In large nonstick skillet cook onion and celery in oil until tender. Add eggplant, zucchini, tomato, olives, vinegar and sugar. Simmer, covered, about 8 minutes or until eggplant is tender. Uncover. Simmer, about 5 minutes more or until most of liquid evaporates. Season with salt and pepper. Cool slightly. Stir in pine nuts or almonds. Serve with crackers.